    {
      "id": "1a76adc5_7772ec7d",
      "file_path": "plugins/reception-plugins/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/distribution/reception/handling/sdc/PSSDConfigurationParametersGroup.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 130,
      "message": "Yes, I guess most of them are mandatory. It's also a good idea to define constants for the default values (if any) for the variables and set the variable to those values at their definition time. For example if we decide that 30 seconds is a good default for polling timeout, define a constant for it:\n\n// Default polling interval in milliseconds\nprivate static final long DEFAULT_POLLING_INTERVAL = 30000;\n\nThen later:\n\nprivate long pollingInterval = DEFAULT_POLLING_INTERVAL;\n\nAlso, if those values are longs, it might be a good idea to check in the validation for zero and negative values.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
